article.headline: Appalachian St. 84, Campbell 71
article.story: BOONE, N.C. (AP) -- D.J. Thompson scored 28 points and Jeremy Clayton had his seventh career double-double Monday to lead Appalachian State to an 84-71 victory over Campbell. Thompson was seven of 12 from the field and shot 10 of 11 from the free-throw line as he helped the 3-2 Mountaineers erase a one-point lead the 3-2 Camels held at halftime. Demetrius Scott also helped Appalachian State with 12 points. Clayton earned the double-double with 10 rebounds and 10 points. Appalachian State took a 5-0 lead, but the Camels overcame it and ended the first half leading 36-35. Ruell Pringle led the Camels with 13 points, including a 3-pointer. Ledell Eackles had 12 points and six rebounds for Campbell, Jonathan Rodriguez had 11 points and Eric Smith scored 10.
